    <header class="resources-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Interview Tips & Tricks</h2>
            <p>Ace your next cybersecurity or IT interview with expert guidance</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <div class="resources-container">
        <a href="/" class="back-btn"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Jobs</a>

        <!-- Before the Interview -->
        <section class="resource-section">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-calendar-check"></i> Before the Interview</h3>
            
            <h4>Research the Company</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Study their website, mission, and values</li>
                <li>Review their tech stack and security infrastructure</li>
                <li>Check recent news articles and press releases</li>
                <li>Look up the interviewers on LinkedIn</li>
                <li>Understand their products, services, and target customers</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Prepare Your Stories</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Use the STAR method (Situation, Task, Action, Result)</li>
                <li>Prepare examples of problem-solving and critical thinking</li>
                <li>Have security incident response stories ready</li>
                <li>Prepare examples of teamwork and collaboration</li>
                <li>Be ready to discuss failures and what you learned</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="tip-box">
                <strong><i class="fas fa-star"></i> Pro Tip:</strong>
                Practice your answers out loud. Record yourself and review to improve your delivery, eliminate filler words, and ensure clarity.
            </div>

            <h4>Technical Preparation</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Review fundamental security concepts (CIA triad, defense in depth, etc.)</li>
                <li>Brush up on common vulnerabilities (OWASP Top 10)</li>
                <li>Practice explaining complex technical concepts simply</li>
                <li>Review relevant certifications and their content</li>
                <li>Be ready to discuss your GitHub projects and portfolio</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- During the Interview -->
        <section class="resource-section">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-comments"></i> During the Interview</h3>
            
            <h4>First Impressions Matter</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Join virtual interviews 5 minutes early to test tech</li>
                <li>Ensure good lighting and a professional background</li>
                <li>Dress professionally (at least business casual)</li>
                <li>Make eye contact and smile</li>
                <li>Have a firm handshake (for in-person interviews)</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Communication Skills</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Listen carefully to the entire question before answering</li>
                <li>Ask clarifying questions when needed</li>
                <li>Think out loud during technical problems</li>
                <li>Be concise but thorough in your answers</li>
                <li>Admit when you don't know something, but show willingness to learn</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="warning-box">
                <strong><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Avoid These Mistakes:</strong>
                Don't badmouth previous employers, don't appear arrogant, don't check your phone, and don't lie about your skills or experience.
            </div>

            <h4>Technical Interview Best Practices</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Walk through your thought process step-by-step</li>
                <li>Ask about constraints and requirements upfront</li>
                <li>Consider edge cases and security implications</li>
                <li>Explain trade-offs in your solutions</li>
                <li>Test your code or logic before finalizing</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Behavioral Interview Techniques</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Keep answers focused and relevant (2-3 minutes max)</li>
                <li>Quantify achievements with specific metrics</li>
                <li>Show enthusiasm and passion for the role</li>
                <li>Demonstrate cultural fit and alignment with company values</li>
                <li>Ask thoughtful questions about the role and team</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Common Cybersecurity Questions -->
        <section class="resource-section">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Common Cybersecurity Interview Questions</h3>
            
            <h4>Technical Questions</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>"Explain the difference between symmetric and asymmetric encryption"</li>
                <li>"What is a SQL injection attack and how do you prevent it?"</li>
                <li>"Describe your incident response process"</li>
                <li>"How would you secure a web application?"</li>
                <li>"What is the principle of least privilege?"</li>
                <li>"Explain the difference between IDS and IPS"</li>
                <li>"How do you stay current with security trends and threats?"</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Scenario-Based Questions</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>"A user reports suspicious activity on their account. What steps do you take?"</li>
                <li>"How would you respond to a ransomware attack?"</li>
                <li>"You discover a critical vulnerability in production. What do you do?"</li>
                <li>"How would you handle a data breach notification?"</li>
                <li>"Describe how you'd conduct a security audit"</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="tip-box">
                <strong><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> Study Tip:</strong>
                Create flashcards for common security terms, protocols, and frameworks. Review them daily in the week leading up to your interview.
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Questions to Ask -->
        <section class="resource-section">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-hand-paper"></i> Questions to Ask the Interviewer</h3>
            
            <h4>About the Role</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>"What does a typical day look like in this position?"</li>
                <li>"What are the biggest challenges facing the security team?"</li>
                <li>"How is success measured in this role?"</li>
                <li>"What security tools and technologies does the team use?"</li>
                <li>"What opportunities for professional development are available?"</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>About the Team & Culture</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>"How large is the security team and how is it structured?"</li>
                <li>"What's the collaboration like between security and development teams?"</li>
                <li>"How does the company prioritize security initiatives?"</li>
                <li>"What's the on-call rotation like?"</li>
                <li>"How does the team handle knowledge sharing and documentation?"</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>About Growth & Future</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>"What are the company's security priorities for the next year?"</li>
                <li>"What career progression opportunities exist?"</li>
                <li>"Does the company support certifications and continued education?"</li>
                <li>"What's the next step in the interview process?"</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- After the Interview -->
        <section class="resource-section">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-paper-plane"></i> After the Interview</h3>
            
            <h4>Follow-Up</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Send a thank-you email within 24 hours</li>
                <li>Reference specific topics discussed in the interview</li>
                <li>Reiterate your interest in the position</li>
                <li>Provide any additional information requested</li>
                <li>Connect with interviewers on LinkedIn (optional)</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Reflection</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Take notes on questions asked and your responses</li>
                <li>Identify areas for improvement</li>
                <li>Note any technical topics to study further</li>
                <li>Keep track of interview timelines and next steps</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="tip-box">
                <strong><i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> Thank-You Email Template:</strong>
                "Dear [Interviewer Name], Thank you for taking the time to speak with me today about the [Position] role. I enjoyed learning about [specific topic discussed] and am excited about the opportunity to contribute to [company's specific initiative]. Please let me know if you need any additional information. I look forward to hearing from you."
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Salary Negotiation -->
        <section class="resource-section">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-dollar-sign"></i> Salary Negotiation Tips</h3>
            
            <ul>
                <li>Research market rates for your role and location (Glassdoor, Payscale, levels.fyi)</li>
                <li>Know your minimum acceptable salary before negotiations</li>
                <li>Let the employer make the first offer when possible</li>
                <li>Consider the entire compensation package (benefits, PTO, remote work, etc.)</li>
                <li>Be prepared to justify your salary expectations with experience and skills</li>
                <li>Negotiate professionally and maintain a positive relationship</li>
                <li>Get the final offer in writing before accepting</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="tip-box">
                <strong><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Negotiation Script:</strong>
                "I'm very excited about this opportunity. Based on my research and experience in [specific skills], I was hoping for a salary in the range of [X-Y]. Is there flexibility in the current offer?"
            </div>
        </section>

